OL,4,Cadmitted to acute wards for mental
OL,5,Chealth issues
OL,7,FResearchers warned the issue "isn't
OL,8,Fgoing to go away", and suggested a
OL,9,Ffocus on "improving care is essential".
OL,11,FExperts also highlight that while the
OL,12,FCovid-19 pandemic had a "profound
OL,13,Fimpact" on youngsters, it is not the
OL,14,F"sole factor" in the increase in
OL,15,Fadmissions.
OL,17,FThe study, led by a team from UCL,
OL,18,Fanalysed data on all admissions for
OL,19,Ffive to 18-year-olds to general acute
OL,20,Fmedical wards in England from 2012 to
OL,21,F2022.
