OL,5,Chealth issues
OL,7,FThese wards assess and treat patients
OL,8,Fand are separate from specialist
OL,9,Fmental health wards. People are
OL,10,Fusually referred to a general acute
OL,11,Fmedical ward from the emergency
OL,12,Fdepartment, or by their GP or
OL,13,Foutpatient clinic.
OL,15,FIn 2021/22, some 342,511 patients aged
OL,16,Ffive to 18 were admitted to hospital
OL,17,Ffor any cause, with 39,925 of these
OL,18,Fdue to mental health concerns.
OL,20,FMore than half (53.4%) were due to
OL,21,Fself-harm, according to the analysis.
