OL,7,FThe team also pointed to "steep
OL,8,Frelative increases" in admissions for
OL,9,Fchildren aged five to 10, with
OL,10,F"striking rates of self-harm in
OL,11,Ffemales".
OL,13,FThey added: "Although absolute numbers
OL,14,Fwere still low, this finding
OL,15,Fhighlights the burden of mental health
OL,16,Fconcerns in children in this
OL,17,Fprepubertal age group."
OL,19,FThere was also a hike in admissions
OL,20,Ffor eating disorders, which jumped
OL,21,Ffrom 478 to 2,938.
